	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Moved some of the parts around, made for a little cleaner board, and managed to fit the third flip-flop under the socket along with the other two.  Also, I think I'll run the PIC high-voltage Vpp signal (for the SuperCIC) to the unused /IRQ line.  I'll have no other use for it, and when I get around to making carts from scratch, I can just put a solder jumper on the board between the Vpp pin on the PIC and /IRQ, so I can disconnect it when I'm done programming (the SuperCIC uses that pin for it's pairing mode detection, so I wouldn't want to leave it connected after programming...)<br /><br /><img src="http://i42.tinypic.com/2yl900p.png" alt="Image" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
