	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I just bought myself a SOIC socket, so I don't really have a need for a SuperCIC programming header on this board... so I thought about what I might do with those pins instead and came to the realization that I should put a CIC lock on-board, so I can talk to SA-1 games.  Can anybody confirm these connections for the SuperCIC lock?  I'm not sure what to do with the extra pins (esp. the REG_TIMEOUT pin, it isn't very well documented in the SuperCIC code what that actually does...).  As for the 50/60Hz and D4 pins, I don't need those since this isn't a console mod, right?  Also, the host reset out, not really sure what that does...<br /><br /><img src="http://i43.tinypic.com/2q8y6fd.png" alt="Image" />

		

		</td>
